event.content:
Huntington Beach Concours d’Elegance

Since 1985 this competition of elegance has raised money for a truly noble cause.  Because it benefits the Children’s Resource Center at the Huntington Beach Public Library!

And it’s not just your typical Sunday-held Concours d’Elegance, it’s a weekend of automotive fun.  So, it includes a Rod & Custom Show on Saturday followed by the competition on Sunday.

Plus this weekend of automotive enthusiasm is complete with motorcycles both days too.  Also, model trains will be on display throughout the weekend for the kids and kids-at-heart to enjoy.

So it’s a weekend of cool cars at the Huntington Central Park with the Rod & Custom Show on Saturday followed by the Huntington Beach Concours d’Elegance on Sunday.

And both days will feature live entertainment, food vendors, and everything you need for a family-friendly good time.

Huntington Beach Concours d’ Elegance

Dates: Saturday, June 5th & Sunday, June 6th, 2021
Location: Huntington Central Park, Huntington Beach, California
Saturday show time: 9 AM to 2 PM
Sunday show time: 9 AM – awards at 2 PM
Admission: $10
Children: Free – under 16 w/ adult
Vehicle registration: HERE (for both days)

*Please note: iDriveSoCal does not host this event.  So if you’d like to learn more about the event please contact the Huntington Beach Concours d’Elegance HERE.  And that includes more specific details about attending, displaying your vehicle, and becoming a vendor or sponsor.
